on. At the beginning of the spring thaw, they used <a title="Stone tool" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stone_tool">stone tools</a> to make V-shaped incisions in tree trunks; they then inserted reeds or concave pieces of bark to run the sap into buckets, which were often made from birch bark.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-history_14-1"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maple_syrup#cite_note-history-14"><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup> The maple sap was concentrated either by dropping hot <a title="Outdoor cooking" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outdoor_cooking">cooking stones</a> into the buckets<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-larkin_16-0"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maple_syrup#cite_note-larkin-16"><span>[</span>16<span>]</span></a></sup> or by leaving them exposed to the cold temperatures overnight and disposing of <a title="Fractional freezing" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractional_freezing">the layer of ice</a> that formed on top. While there was widespread <a title="Agriculture in Mesoamerica" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agriculture_in_Mesoamerica">Agriculture in Mesoamerica</a> and the Southeast and Southwest regions of the United States, the production of maple syrup is one of very few agricultural processes in the Northeast that did not come European colonists.\r\n\r\n[/dt_sc_tab] [dt_sc_tab title="Is it healthy?" icon="fa-key"] There are a lot of scientific studies going on right now specifically on health benefits of maple sugar over any other sweeteners. One of the most surprising is that when combined with baking soda it is actually used as the delivery system for the alkaline baking soda to treat cancer. Some cases of doing this report that their cancer all but disappeared! This is just one of many treatments being looked at for future patients. [/dt_sc_tab] [dt_sc_tab title="Why Organic?" icon="fa-thumbs-o-up"] In an age with kids and adults that have serious health problems due to modern practices 