(3577, 1, '2014-05-19 10:35:20', '2014-05-19 10:35:20', '[dt_sc_fancy_ul style="tick" variation="blue"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is a sweet, water like liquid that is collected from the maple trees</li>\r\n	<li>Forty gallons of sap is gathered to make one gallon of maple syrup</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sugar is made by boiling the syrup longer, to reduce the water content and then stirring until a sugar is formed</li>\r\n	<li>A maple tree should be about 40 years old or 8 inches in diameter to be tapped</li>\r\n	<li>The sap "runs" when the temperatures fall below freezing at night and then thaws during the day. The freezing point is 32 degrees F</li>\r\n	<li>The trees release their sap in the springtime (March to April) when they start to wake up from the long winter''s nap</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is what the tree uses to make buds</li>\r\n	<li>When the trees have made buds, the time to sugar has stopped. The syrup will become very bitter to taste</li>\r\n	<li>During the summer the trees make starch which is stored and turned to sugar</li>\r\n	<li>Trees are tapped by drilling a hole and inserting a spout to catch the sap in a bucket or pipeline. The spout is carefully tapped into the hole with a small hammer</li>\r\n	<li>A new tap hole must be made each year</li>\r\n	<li>Healthy trees heal old tap wounds within three years and have large crowns of branches and leaves during the summer</li>\r\n	<li>Tapping doesn''t hurt the tree in any way  studies show the trees that are tapped year after year live just as long, and stay just as strong and healthy</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n[/dt_sc_fancy_ul]', 'Maple syrup at a glance ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3572-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-19 10:35:20', '2014-05-19 10:35:20', '', 3572, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3578, 1, '2014-05-19 10:40:21', '2014-05-19 10:40:21', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-maple-syrup.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3783 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-maple-syrup-150x100.png" alt="why-maple-syrup" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span style="color: #A33B03;">Rich in iron, potassium, magnesium &amp; phosphorus - and has a higher calcium content that milk</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #A33B03;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" />Contains small amounts<span class="apple-converted-space"></span><span class="textexposedshow">of amino acids, proteins, vitamins B2, B5 &amp; niacin</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #A33B03;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span class="textexposedshow">Has only 40 calories per Tablespoon. Honey has 45, white sugar has 55 &amp; corn sugar has 60</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #A33B03;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span class="textexposedshow">Has compounds with similar anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidant properties as blueberries, green tea, red wine and broccoli</span>; <span class="textexposedshow">these compounds have been shown to fight cancer, diabetes and bacterial illnesses</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #A33B03;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" />Con