(3582, 1, '2014-05-19 10:45:12', '2014-05-19 10:45:12', '[dt_sc_accordion_group]\r\n[dt_sc_toggle_framed title="Iron, Potassium, Magnesium & Phosphorus"]Maple Syrup contains iron, potassium, magnesium & phosphorus - and has a higher calcium content that milk; it also contains small amounts of amino acids, proteins & vitamins B2, B5 & niacin[/dt_sc_toggle_framed]\r\n[dt_sc_toggle_framed title="40 calories per Tablespoon"] Maple Syrup only has 40 calories per Tablespoon. Honey has 45, white sugar has 55 & corn sugar has 60[/dt_sc_toggle_framed]\r\n[dt_sc_toggle_framed title="Anti-inflammatory or Anti-oxidant properties"]Researchers have identified compounds in maple syrup with similar anti-inflammatory or anti-oxidant properties as blueberries, green tea and broccoli; These compounds have been shown to fight cancer, diabetes and bacterial illnesses[/dt_sc_toggle_framed]\r\n[dt_sc_toggle_framed title="Carbohydrate-hydrolyzing enzymes"]Scientists have found that maple syrup''s natural phenols  potentially beneficial antioxidant compounds  inhibit two carbohydrate-hydrolyzing enzymes that are relevant to type 2 diabetes[/dt_sc_toggle_framed]\r\n[dt_sc_toggle_framed title="Easiest for our metabolism"]Maple syrup, compared to refined sugars, is the easiest for our metabolism to digest[/dt_sc_toggle_framed]\r\n[/dt_sc_accordion_group]', 'Why Maple Syrup? ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3578-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-19 10:45:12', '2014-05-19 10:45:12', '', 3578, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3578-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
