(3807, 1, '2014-06-27 06:49:24', '2014-06-27 06:49:24', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/franchise-inquiries.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3767" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/franchise-inquiries-300x187.png" alt="franchise-inquiries" width="150" height="94" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #011917;"><strong>Thank you for your interest in Fluffy Maple Puff Puffs!</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #011917;">We are a growing successfulmobile food franchisorwhose mission is to offer a nutritious, healthy and delicious alternative to American favorite concessions, in the form of gourmet maple treats, made with organic pure maple syrup, and organic, all natural, dye-free, kosher, vegan and gluten<img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-3940" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/greenleaf-150x150.png" alt="greenleaf" width="150" height="150" /> free ingredients. Our franchisees recognize that theFluffy Maple Puff Puffs concept is completely unique and answers a growing demand for amazing, tasty sweet treats that are also wholesome and nourishing.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #011917;">We welcome enthusiastic entrepreneurs who can help us fulfill our maplelicious vision and want to join a successful <a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/mapleleaf.png"><span style="color: #011917;"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-3947" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/mapleleaf-150x150.png" alt="mapleleaf" width="150" height="150" /></span></a>venture that celebrates healthy in everything we do!</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #011917;">If you are interested in becoming aFluffy Maple Puff Puffs franchisee, we would love to hear from you.</span></p>\n[dt_sc_one_half first]\n\n<span style="color: #011917;">Please contact Randi Shannon at 305 491 4597 for inquiries, or fill out the form below, and we will get in touch with you within 24 hours!</span>\n\n<span style="color: #011917;">Thank you!</span>\n\n[contact-form-7 id="3527" title="Franchise maintenance mode"]\n\n[/dt_sc_one_half]\n\n[dt_sc_one_half]\n\n<span style="color: #011917;">For current franchise owner, please log in for all your orders,</span>\n\n<span style="color: #011917;">Thank you</span>\n\n<span style="color: #011917;">Comming soon!</span>\n\n[/dt_sc_one_half]', 'Franchise inquiries', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3291-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 06:49:24', '2014-06-27 06:49:24', '', 3291, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3291-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3808, 1, '2014-06-17 15:08:43', '2014-06-17 15:08:43', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/franchise-inquiries.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3767" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/franchise-inquiries-300x187.png" alt="franchise-inquiries" width="150" height="94" /></a>\r\n\r\nWe are a growing successful mobile food franchisor whose mission is to offer a nutritious, healthy and delicious alternative to American favorite concessions, in the form of gourmet maple treats, made with organic pure maple syrup, and organic, all natural, dye-free, kosher, vegan and gluten free ingredients. Our franchisees recognize that the Fluffy Maple Puff Puffs concept is completely unique and answers a growing demand for amazing, tasty sweet treats that are also wholesome and nourishing. We welcome enthusiastic entrepreneurs who can help us fulfill our maplelicious vision and want to join a successful venture that celebrates healthy in everything we do!\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in becoming a Fluffy Maple Puff Puffs franchisee, we would love to hear from you.\r\n\r\nPlease contact Randi Shannon at 305 491 4597 for inquiries, or fill out the form below, and we will get in touch with you within 24 hours!\r\n\r\nThank you\r\n\r\n[contact-form-7 id="3483" title="Untitled"]', 'Franchise inquiries', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3291-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-17 15:08:43', '2014-06-17 15:08:43', '', 3291, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3291-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3809, 1, '2014-06-17 15:08:52', '2014-06-17 15:08:52', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/history-of-maple-syrup.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-3776 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/history-of-maple-syrup-150x100.png" alt="history-of-maple-syrup" width="150" height="100" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Early settlers in the U.S. Northeast and Canada learned about sugar maples from Native Americans. While there are written accounts of maple sugaring in North America dating back to 1557, the exact origins of sugaring are unknown. Various legends exist to explain the initial discovery. One is that the chief of a tribe threw a tomahawk at a tree, sap ran out and his wife boiled venison in the liquid. Another version holds that Native Americans stumbled on sap running from a broken maple branch.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">History also remains silent on whether Native Americans boiled down the sap to maple sugar, or if these techniques were introduced by the French explorers and missionaries. But by the 1700s, Native Americans and European settlers alike were using iron and copper kettles to make syrup and sugar. In 1755, a young colonist was captured and "adopted" by a small group of natives in the region that is now Ohio. In 1799 he published his story, in which he included a description of how the Native Americans made maple sugar.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">In the late 1700s and early 1800s, maple sap was produced into maple sugar, a granular, solid block of maple that had a long shelf-life and could be easily transported. Maple sugar was promoted by the Quakers and abolitionists as an alternative to West Indian slave-produced cane sugar; Thomas Jefferson even started a maple plantation at Monticello in 1791.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">It wasnt until the Civil War that the maple syrup industry was born, with the introduction of the tin cans and the invention of metal spouts and evaporator pans. Most early producers were dairy farmers who made maple syrup and sugar during the off-season of the farm for their own use and for extra income.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Technology remain largely the same for the next century until the energy crisis of the 1970s forced maple syrup producers to change their labor-intensive process. With another surge of technological breakthroughs, tubing systems were perfected, taking the sap directly from the tree to the sugarhouse. Vacuum pumps were added to the tubing systems, pre-heaters were developed to "recycle" heat lost in the steam, and reverse-osmosis filters were designed to take a portion of the water out of the sap before it was boiled. And these technological advances continue today, ever moving the story of maple syrup forward.</p>', 'History of maple syrup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3570-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-17 15:08:52', '2014-06-17 15:08:52', '', 3570, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3570-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3810, 1, '2014-06-17 15:08:58', '2014-06-17 15:08:58', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3777 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance-150x100.png" alt="maple-syrup-at-a-glance" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_fancy_ul style="tick" variation="blue"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is a sweet, water like liquid that is collected from the maple trees</li>\r\n	<li>Forty gallons of sap is gathered to make one gallon of maple syrup</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sugar is made by boiling the syrup longer, to reduce the water content and then stirring until a sugar is formed</li>\r\n	<li>A maple tree should be about 40 years old or 8 inches in diameter to be tapped</li>\r\n	<li>The sap "runs" when the temperatures fall below freezing at night and then thaws during the day. The freezing point is 32 degrees F</li>\r\n	<li>The trees release their sap in the springtime (March to April) when they start to wake up from the long winter''s nap</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is what the tree uses to make buds</li>\r\n	<li>When the trees have made buds, the time to sugar has stopped. The syrup will become very bitter to taste</li>\r\n	<li>During the summer the trees make starch which is stored and turned to sugar</li>\r\n	<li>Trees are tapped by drilling a hole and inserting a spout to catch the sap in a bucket or pipeline. The spout is carefully tapped into the hole with a small hammer</li>\r\n	<li>A new tap hole must be made each year</li>\r\n	<li>Healthy trees heal old tap wounds within three years and have large crowns of branches and leaves during the summer</li>\r\n	<li>Tapping doesn''t hurt the tree in any way  studies show the trees that are tapped year after year live just as long, and stay just as strong and healthy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/dt_sc_fancy_ul]', 'Maple syrup at a glance ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3572-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-17 15:08:58', '2014-06-17 15:08:58', '', 3572, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3811, 1, '2014-06-17 15:09:15', '2014-06-17 15:09:15', '<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/current-franchise-owners.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-3774 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/current-franchise-owners-150x100.png" alt="current-franchise-owners" width="150" height="100" /></a></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>For current franchise owner, please log in for all your orders,</em></strong></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong><em></em></strong></h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>Thank you</em></strong></h2>', 'Current franchise owners', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3621-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-17 15:09:15', '2014-06-17 15:09:15', '', 3621, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3621-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3812, 1, '2014-06-17 15:11:25', '2014-06-17 15:11:25', '<h2><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/organic-maple-cotton-candy.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3764 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/organic-maple-cotton-candy-150x89.png" alt="organic-maple-cotton-candy" width="150" height="89" /></a></h2>\r\n<span style="color: #a33070;"><span style="color: #a33070;">Our gourmet maple cotton candy was the first Puff Puff in our family, and is a very dear one to us! </span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #a33070;">It might look like cotton candy, but it is not <a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/cotton-candy-character.png"><img class="alignleft size-full" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/cotton-candy-character-191x300.png" alt="cotton-candy-character" width="191" height="300" /></a>quite. There is not one granule of processed sugar of any kind in our maple cotton candy. Its made from 100% pure organic maple sugar, nothing more and nothing less. Just the raw unprocessed wonderful maple goodness. All natural, completely non-allergenic, with absolutely no chemicals or artificial dyes.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #a33070;">The process goes like this: maple tree - &gt; maple sap - &gt; maple syrup - &gt; maple sugar - &gt; Fluffy Maple Puff Puffs maple cotton candy!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #a33070;">As for our flavored maple cotton candy, all the flavors that we use are organic, natural, kosher, vegan, gluten free, corn free and soy free. They all are completely dye free and chemical free as well.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #a33070;">A delicious super healthy treat</span>\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_hr_invisible]\r\n\r\n[dt_hr_title tag="h2"]Our Flavors[/dt_hr_title]\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth first]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Cinnamon Maple" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/cinnamon-maple.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Coconut Maple Chocolate" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/coconut-maple-chocolate.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Coconut Maple Mango" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/coconut-maple-mango.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Dulce de Leche Maple" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/dulce-de-leche-maple.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth first]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Maple Blueberry" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/maple-blueberry.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Maple Cofee" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/maple-coffee.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Maple Pumpkin Pie" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/maple-pumpkin-pie.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_fourth]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Pure Maple Syrup" image="http://fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Pure_Maple_Syrup.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_fourth]', 'Organic Maple Cotton Candy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3608-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-17 15:11:25', '2014-06-17 15:11:25', '', 3608, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3608-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
