(3891, 1, '2014-06-27 06:29:31', '2014-06-27 06:29:31', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3777 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance-150x100.png" alt="maple-syrup-at-a-glance" width="150" height="100" /></a>\n\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></a>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;">Maple sap is a sweet, water like liquid that is collected from the maple trees</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Forty gallons of sap is gathered to make one gallon of maple syrup</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Maple sugar is made by boiling the syrup longer, to reduce the water content and then stirring until a sugaris formed</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>A maple tree should be about 40 years old or 8 inches in diameter to be tapped</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>The sap "runs" when the temperatures fall below freezing at night and then thaws during the day, usually between March and April</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Maple sap is what the tree uses to make buds</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>When the trees have made buds, the time to sugar has stopped; the syrup will become very bitter to taste</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>During the summer the trees make starch which is stored and turned to sugar</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Trees are tapped by drilling a hole and inserting a spout to catch the sap in a bucket or pipeline. The spout is carefully tapped into the hole with a small hammer</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>A new tap hole must be made each year</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Healthy trees heal old tap wounds within three years and have large crowns of branches and leaves during the summer</span>\n\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Tapping doesn''t hurt the tree in any way  studies show the trees that are tapped year after year live just as long, and stay just as strong and healthy</span>', 'Maple syrup at a glance ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3572-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 06:29:31', '2014-06-27 06:29:31', '', 3572, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3572-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3892, 1, '2014-06-20 09:17:50', '2014-06-20 09:17:50', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3777 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance-150x100.png" alt="maple-syrup-at-a-glance" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="43" height="47" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMaple syrup at a glace\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_fancy_ul style="tick" variation="blue"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is a sweet, water like liquid that is collected from the maple trees</li>\r\n	<li>Forty gallons of sap is gathered to make one gallon of maple syrup</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sugar is made by boiling the syrup longer, to reduce the water content and then stirring until a sugar is formed</li>\r\n	<li>A maple tree should be about 40 years old or 8 inches in diameter to be tapped</li>\r\n	<li>The sap "runs" when the temperatures fall below freezing at night and then thaws during the day. The freezing point is 32 degrees F</li>\r\n	<li>The trees release their sap in the springtime (March to April) when they start to wake up from the long winter''s nap</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is what the tree uses to make buds</li>\r\n	<li>When the trees have made buds, the time to sugar has stopped. The syrup will become very bitter to taste</li>\r\n	<li>During the summer the trees make starch which is stored and turned to sugar</li>\r\n	<li>Trees are tapped by drilling a hole and inserting a spout to catch the sap in a bucket or pipeline. The spout is carefully tapped into the hole with a small hammer</li>\r\n	<li>A new tap hole must be made each year</li>\r\n	<li>Healthy trees heal old tap wounds within three years and have large crowns of branches and leaves during the summer</li>\r\n	<li>Tapping doesn''t hurt the tree in any way  studies show the trees that are tapped year after year live just as long, and stay just as strong and healthy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/dt_sc_fancy_ul]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Maple syrup at a glance ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3572-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 09:17:50', '2014-06-20 09:17:50', '', 3572, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3893, 1, '2014-06-20 09:18:44', '2014-06-20 09:18:44', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3777 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance-150x100.png" alt="maple-syrup-at-a-glance" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="15" height="16" /></a>Maple syrup at a glace\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_fancy_ul style="tick" variation="blue"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is a sweet, water like liquid that is collected from the maple trees</li>\r\n	<li>Forty gallons of sap is gathered to make one gallon of maple syrup</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sugar is made by boiling the syrup longer, to reduce the water content and then stirring until a sugar is formed</li>\r\n	<li>A maple tree should be about 40 years old or 8 inches in diameter to be tapped</li>\r\n	<li>The sap "runs" when the temperatures fall below freezing at night and then thaws during the day. The freezing point is 32 degrees F</li>\r\n	<li>The trees release their sap in the springtime (March to April) when they start to wake up from the long winter''s nap</li>\r\n	<li>Maple sap is what the tree uses to make buds</li>\r\n	<li>When the trees have made buds, the time to sugar has stopped. The syrup will become very bitter to taste</li>\r\n	<li>During the summer the trees make starch which is stored and turned to sugar</li>\r\n	<li>Trees are tapped by drilling a hole and inserting a spout to catch the sap in a bucket or pipeline. The spout is carefully tapped into the hole with a small hammer</li>\r\n	<li>A new tap hole must be made each year</li>\r\n	<li>Healthy trees heal old tap wounds within three years and have large crowns of branches and leaves during the summer</li>\r\n	<li>Tapping doesn''t hurt the tree in any way  studies show the trees that are tapped year after year live just as long, and stay just as strong and healthy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/dt_sc_fancy_ul]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Maple syrup at a glance ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3572-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-20 09:18:44', '2014-06-20 09:18:44', '', 3572, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
