(4025, 1, '2014-06-25 10:36:07', '2014-06-25 10:36:07', '<img class="aligncenter wp-image-3759" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/about-us1-300x170.png" alt="about-us1" width="150" height="85" />\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #be2525;">Our story started with our love for everything maple and everything healthy! Three friends with a passion for everything sweet, delicious, nourishing and beneficial for you; we are Matt, Randi and Andreea, and we are the Fluffy Maple Puff Puff family!</span></p>\r\n[dt_sc_one_third first]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Andreea" image="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/andreeapng.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_third]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_third]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Matt" image="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/mattpng.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_third]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_one_third]\r\n[dt_sc_team name="Randi" image="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Randipng.png" /]\r\n[/dt_sc_one_third]\r\n\r\n[dt_sc_hr_invisible]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #be2525;">Fluffy Maple Puff Puffs was born in March of 2014, and we sell organic, non-GMO, all natural, vegan, gluten-free, kosher, pure maple syrup gourmet treats.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="alignnone wp-image-3662" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/all3characters.png" alt="all3characters" width="200" height="175" /></p>\r\n<img class="alignleft" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/syrup.png" alt="placehold" />\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #8a0096;">The organic maple syrup is the superstar in all of our puff puffs, an amazing superfood that makes our puff puffs completely special and unique on the entire American market.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #8a0096;">We wanted to take good old American favorite sweets and snacks, and completely reinvent them. We replaced GMO with fully certified organic, we removed chemicals and dyes by opting for all natural and dye-free ingredients instead, but most of all, we made a point to replace processed refined sugars with the most delicious and wholesome raw sweetener known to man: maple syrup!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #03581f;">We celebrate maple and its mouth watering taste in every single one of our recipes, and we absolutely love that everything we offer is not only a source of delightful taste, but also an energizing, invigorating source of health as well.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="alignright wp-image-3666" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/redmapleleaf.png" alt="redmapleleaf" width="200" height="213" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #03581f;">Being a natural unrefined sugar, with less calories than even honey, maple syrup is full of nutrients, minerals, and compounds that have anti-oxidant, anti-inflammatory, anti-diabetes and anti-cancer properties. Maple syrup has now acquired the status of a superfood, and has joined the ranks of broccoli and berries in fighting for a stronger immune system.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #0015a8;">This is why we do this! We want to glorify the all amazing maple in all of our puff puffs, and put a completely new healthy spin on cotton candy, popcorn, ice cream, and many new treats we are working on.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #0015a8;">Our maple puff puffs are truly the next big thing, and we are so excited to see everyone fall in love with everything maple as well!</span></p>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-25 10:36:07', '2014-06-25 10:36:07', '', 2, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4026, 1, '2014-06-25 10:41:38', '2014-06-25 10:41:38', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/history-of-maple-syrup.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-3776 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/history-of-maple-syrup-150x100.png" alt="history-of-maple-syrup" width="150" height="100" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/yellowleaf.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-3885" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/yellowleaf.png" alt="yellowleaf" width="86" height="95" /></a></p>\r\n<span style="color: #03581f;">Early settlers in the U.S. Northeast and Canada learned about sugar maples from Native Americans. While there are written accounts of maple sugaring in North America dating back to 1557, the exact origins of sugaring are unknown. Various legends exist to explain the initial discovery. One is that the chief of a tribe threw a tomahawk at a tree, sap ran out and his wife boiled venison in the liquid. Another version holds that Native Americans stumbled on sap running from a broken maple branch.</span><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-3886" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mapletree-254x300.png" alt="mapletree" width="254" height="300" />\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #0015a8;">By the 1700s, Native Americans and European settlers alike were using iron and copper kettles to make syrup and sugar.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #be2525;">In the late 1700s and early 1800s, maple sap was produced into maple sugar, a granular, solid block of maple that had a long shelf-life and could be easily transported.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #8a0096;">It wasnt until the Civil War that the maple syrup industry was born, with the introduction of the tin cans and the invention of metal spouts and evaporator pans. Technology remained largely the same for the next century until the energy crisis of the 1970s forced maple syrup producers to change their labor-intensive process. With another surge of technological breakthroughs, tubing systems were perfected, taking the sap directly from the tree to the sugarhouse. Vacuum pumps were added to the tubing systems, pre-heaters were developed to "recycle" heat lost in the steam, and reverse-osmosis filters were designed to take a portion of the water out of the sap before it was boiled. And these technological advances continue today, ever moving the story of maple syrup forward.</span>', 'History of maple syrup', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3570-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-25 10:41:38', '2014-06-25 10:41:38', '', 3570, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3570-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4027, 1, '2014-06-25 10:46:23', '2014-06-25 10:46:23', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3777 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance-150x100.png" alt="maple-syrup-at-a-glance" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #be2525;">Maple sap is a sweet, water like liquid that is collected from the maple trees</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #03581f;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Forty gallons of sap is gathered to make one gallon of maple syrup</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #8a0096;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Maple sugar is made by boiling the syrup longer, to reduce the water content and then stirring until a sugaris formed</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #0015a8;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>A maple tree should be about 40 years old or 8 inches in diameter to be tapped</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #be2525;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>The sap "runs" when the temperatures fall below freezing at night and then thaws during the day, usually between March and April</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #03581f;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Maple sap is what the tree uses to make buds</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #8a0096;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>When the trees have made buds, the time to sugar has stopped; the syrup will become very bitter to taste</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #0015a8;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>During the summer the trees make starch which is stored and turned to sugar</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #be2525;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Trees are tapped by drilling a hole and inserting a spout to catch the sap in a bucket or pipeline. The spout is carefully tapped into the hole with a small hammer</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #03581f;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>A new tap hole must be made each year</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #8a0096;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Healthy trees heal old tap wounds within three years and have large crowns of branches and leaves during the summer</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #0015a8;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #000000;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Tapping doesn''t hurt the tree in any way  studies show the trees that are tapped year after year live just as long, and stay just as strong and healthy</span>', 'Maple syrup at a glance ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3572-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-25 10:46:23', '2014-06-25 10:46:23', '', 3572, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
