(4100, 1, '2014-06-27 06:29:55', '2014-06-27 06:29:55', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3777 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/maple-syrup-at-a-glance-150x100.png" alt="maple-syrup-at-a-glance" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;">Maple sap is a sweet, water like liquid that is collected from the maple trees</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Forty gallons of sap is gathered to make one gallon of maple syrup</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Maple sugar is made by boiling the syrup longer, to reduce the water content and then stirring until a sugaris formed</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>A maple tree should be about 40 years old or 8 inches in diameter to be tapped</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>The sap "runs" when the temperatures fall below freezing at night and then thaws during the day, usually between March and April</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Maple sap is what the tree uses to make buds</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>When the trees have made buds, the time to sugar has stopped; the syrup will become very bitter to taste</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>During the summer the trees make starch which is stored and turned to sugar</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Trees are tapped by drilling a hole and inserting a spout to catch the sap in a bucket or pipeline. The spout is carefully tapped into the hole with a small hammer</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>A new tap hole must be made each year</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Healthy trees heal old tap wounds within three years and have large crowns of branches and leaves during the summer</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #311b05;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png"><span style="color: #311b05;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3890" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/redleaf.png" alt="redleaf" width="25" height="27" /></span></a>Tapping doesn''t hurt the tree in any way  studies show the trees that are tapped year after year live just as long, and stay just as strong and healthy</span>', 'Maple syrup at a glance ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3572-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 06:29:55', '2014-06-27 06:29:55', '', 3572, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4101, 1, '2014-06-27 06:33:12', '2014-06-27 06:33:12', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-maple-syrup.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3783 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-maple-syrup-150x100.png" alt="why-maple-syrup" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span style="color: #f0712a;">Rich in iron, potassium, magnesium &amp; phosphorus - and has a higher calcium content that milk</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" />Contains small amounts<span class="apple-converted-space"></span><span class="textexposedshow">of amino acids, proteins, vitamins B2, B5 &amp; niacin</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span class="textexposedshow">Has only 40 calories per Tablespoon. Honey has 45, white sugar has 55 &amp; corn sugar has 60</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span class="textexposedshow">Has compounds with similar anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidant properties as blueberries, green tea, red wine and broccoli</span>; <span class="textexposedshow">these compounds have been shown to fight cancer, diabetes and bacterial illnesses</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" />Contains natural phenols, commonly found in berries, that have been found to inhibit two carbohydrate-hydrolyzing enzymes that are relevant to type 2 diabetes</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #38042f;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" />It is the easiest type of sugar for our metabolism to digest</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3905" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph1.jpg" alt="graph1" width="640" height="389" /></a> <a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3906 size-full" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph2.jpg" alt="graph2" width="640" height="390" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Why Maple Syrup? ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3578-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 06:33:12', '2014-06-27 06:33:12', '', 3578, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3578-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4102, 1, '2014-06-27 06:33:36', '2014-06-27 06:33:36', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-maple-syrup.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3783 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-maple-syrup-150x100.png" alt="why-maple-syrup" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span style="color: #f0712a;">Rich in iron, potassium, magnesium &amp; phosphorus - and has a higher calcium content that milk</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" />Contains small amounts<span class="apple-converted-space"></span><span class="textexposedshow">of amino acids, proteins, vitamins B2, B5 &amp; niacin</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span class="textexposedshow">Has only 40 calories per Tablespoon. Honey has 45, white sugar has 55 &amp; corn sugar has 60</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span class="textexposedshow">Has compounds with similar anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidant properties as blueberries, green tea, red wine and broccoli</span>; <span class="textexposedshow">these compounds have been shown to fight cancer, diabetes and bacterial illnesses</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #f0712a;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" />Contains natural phenols, commonly found in berries, that have been found to inhibit two carbohydrate-hydrolyzing enzymes that are relevant to type 2 diabetes</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #38042f;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3900" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleaf.png" alt="" width="25" height="24" /><span style="color: #f0712a;">It is the easiest type of sugar for our metabolism to digest</span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3905" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph1.jpg" alt="graph1" width="640" height="389" /></a> <a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3906 size-full" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/graph2.jpg" alt="graph2" width="640" height="390" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Why Maple Syrup? ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3578-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 06:33:36', '2014-06-27 06:33:36', '', 3578, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3578-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4103, 1, '2014-06-27 06:34:33', '2014-06-27 06:34:33', '<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-organic.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3784 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/why-organic-150x100.png" alt="why-organic" width="150" height="100" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" /><span style="color: #093504;">No chemical fertilizers or pesticides used in the maple bush or in the area w<span class="textexposedshow">here organic products are processed. If necessary, agricultural lime, wood ash or natural fertilizers may be used</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" /><span class="textexposedshow">A limit of three tapholes per tree. No over-tapping. No germicides (paraformaldehyde) in tapholes</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" /><span class="textexposedshow">Selective and correct use of vacuum tubing</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" /><span class="textexposedshow">Avoidance at all times of frequent use of machinery to prevent injury to the surfaced roots</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" />No lead or lead solder used in the equipment required for processing organic maple products; consequently, there is no lead in the finished product. Lead can be a concern with some conventional maple syrup producers using older equipment</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" />During the running season, the line system must be cleaned with natural biodegradable products</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" />No synthetic chemical products used to control foam during boiling</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" />No treatment of sap with ultra-violet radiation. No microwave cooking of processed organic maple products</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" />The maple syrup is strained though a fine polyethylene membrane</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" />Maple syrup is stores in stainless steel, instead of galvanized steel drums</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #093504;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3908" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/orangeleafsimple.png" alt="orangeleafsimple" width="25" height="28" />Each bottle of organic maple syrup is traceable. Using the lot #, one is able to determine who the manufacturer is, and when the syrup was produced</span>', 'Why Organic?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3586-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 06:34:33', '2014-06-27 06:34:33', '', 3586, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3586-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4104, 1, '2014-06-27 06:36:16', '2014-06-27 06:36:16', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ourpuffpuffs.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-3779 size-thumbnail" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ourpuffpuffs-150x95.png" alt="ourpuffpuffs" width="150" height="95" /></a></p>\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/all3characters.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-3685" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/all3characters-300x263.png" alt="all3characters" width="200" height="175" /></a>\n\n<span style="color: #ff3900;">Organic pure maple syrup is the hero in all of our delicious Puff Puffs! It is our main ingredient in all of our recipes, and we absolutely love it! Every Puff Puff is certified organic, non-GMO, all natural, vegan, gluten free, kosher, and is completely free of all chemicals and dyes. Our mission is to put a healthy spin on all of your favorite treats, and serve them to you with so much love and joy!</span>\n\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/cotton-candy60px.png"><img class="alignleft size-full" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/cotton-candy60px.png" alt="cotton-candy60px" width="38" height="60" /></a>\n\n<a title="Organic Maple Cotton Candy" href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/organic-maple-cotton-candy/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">Organic Maple Cotton Candy</span></a>\n\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/popcorn60px.png"><img class="alignleft size-full" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/popcorn60px.png" alt="popcorn60px" width="45" height="60" /></a>\n\n<a title="Organic Maple Popcorn" href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/organic-maple-popcorn/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #99cc00;">Organic Maple Ice Popcorn</span></a>\n\n<a href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ice-cream-60px.png"><img class="alignleft size-full" src="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ice-cream-60px.png" alt="ice-cream-60px" width="39" height="60" /></a>\n\n<a title="Organic Maple Ice Cream" href="http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/organic-maple-ice-cream/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #00ccff;">Organic Maple Ice Cream</span></a>', 'Our Puff Puffs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '3421-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-06-27 06:36:16', '2014-06-27 06:36:16', '', 3421, 'http://www.fluffymaplepuffpuffs.com/uncategorized/3421-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
